---
import Link from "../components/Link.astro";
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <section class="privacy">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      Last updated: May 19, 2026.
    </p>

    <h2>Controller</h2>
    <p>
      The controller responsible for this website under the EU General Data
      Protection Regulation (GDPR) is Henry Gressmann. Contact information is
      available in the <Link href="/impressum">
        Impressum/Legal Notice
      </Link>.
    </p>

    <h2>General Information</h2>
    <p>
      This is a private website and blog. I process personal data only where it
      is necessary to provide this website, keep it secure, respond to messages,
      or understand basic, privacy-friendly usage statistics. I do not sell
      personal data.
      <br />
      This website does not intentionally set tracking cookies. If this changes,
      this privacy policy will be updated accordingly.
    </p>

    <h2>Your data protection rights</h2>
    <p>
      As a data subject, you have the right of access, rectification, erasure,
      restriction of processing, data portability, and objection to processing of
      your personal data. If processing is based on consent, you may withdraw
      that consent at any time with effect for the future.
      <br />
      Please send requests, objections, or withdrawals informally to:
      <Link href="mailto:contact@henrygressmann.de">contact@henrygressmann.de</Link>. <br
      />
      You may at any time lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, e.g. the
      competent supervisory authority in the federal state of your residence or
      the authority responsible for me as the controller.
      <br />
      A list of supervisory authorities (for the non-public sector) with address can
      be found at
      <Link
        href="https://www.bfdi.bund.de/DE/Service/Anschriften/Laender/Laender-node.html"
      >
        www.bfdi.bund.de/DE/Service/Anschriften/Laender/Laender-node.html
      </Link>.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact by Email</h2>
    <p>
      If you contact me by email, I process the data you provide, such as your
      email address, name, message content, and technical metadata, to respond to
      your request. The legal basis is Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR. If your
      message relates to a contractual or pre-contractual matter, the legal basis
      may also be Art. 6 para. 1 lit. b GDPR.
      <br />
      I keep email correspondence only as long as necessary for the relevant
      purpose, unless legal retention obligations apply.
    </p>

    <h2>Meetings</h2>
    <p>
      The meeting page embeds Cal.com. When you visit that page or schedule a
      meeting, personal data such as your IP address, browser information, name,
      email address, selected time, and message content may be processed by
      Cal.com. This is used to provide scheduling functionality. The legal basis
      is Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR, and where scheduling concerns a contractual
      or pre-contractual request, Art. 6 para. 1 lit. b GDPR.
      <br />
      Cal.com's privacy policy is available at <Link href="https://cal.com/privacy">
        cal.com/privacy
      </Link>.
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      This website uses a privacy-friendly analytics. The analytics are used to
      understand basic usage of this website and improve its content and technical performance.
      The legal basis is my legitimate interest under Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR.
      <br />
      Analytics data is processed in anonymized or aggregated form. I do not use
      the analytics setup to create personal profiles, track visitors across
      third-party websites, or store persistent personal identifiers. No analytics
      cookies are intentionally set by this website.
    </p>

    <h2>Hosting</h2>
    <p>
      To deliver this website, technical access data may be processed in server
      log files. This can include your IP address, date and time of the request,
      requested URL, referrer, HTTP status code, amount of data transferred, and
      information about the browser and operating system. This processing is
      necessary to display the website and ensure stability, performance, and
      security. The legal basis is Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR.
      <br />
      <br />
      I use the following providers to make this website available:
      <br />
    </p>

    <br />
    <h3>Hetzner Online GmbH</h3>
    <p>
      Industriestr. 25, 91710 Gunzenhausen
      <br />
      <Link href="https://www.hetzner.com/de/rechtliches/datenschutz">
        www.hetzner.com/de/rechtliches/datenschutz
      </Link>
    </p>

    <br />
    <h3>GitHub Pages</h3>
    <p>
      GitHub, Inc., 88 Colin P Kelly Jr St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA. GitHub
      Pages may be used to host static files such as images, fonts, JavaScript,
      and documents. GitHub may process technical access data for this purpose.
      This is in line with my legitimate interest under Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f
      GDPR, so that I do not have to operate all infrastructure myself. The
      server location may be the USA. For further information on how to object or
      remove data on GitHub, you can check:
      <Link
        href="https://docs.github.com/en/github/site-policy/github-privacy-statement"
      >
        docs.github.com/en/github/site-policy/github-privacy-statement
      </Link>
      <br />
      You have the right to object to this processing. Whether the objection is
      successful needs to be determined through a balancing of interests. The data
      will be deleted as soon as the purpose of its processing has been fulfilled,
      unless legal retention obligations apply. Processing of the data specified
      in this section is neither legally nor contractually required. However, the
      functionality of the website is not guaranteed without this processing.
      GitHub has implemented compliance measures for international data transfers,
      including EU Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs). More info can be found at:
      <Link href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies">
        https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies
      </Link>
    </p>

    <br />
    <h3>Cloudflare</h3>
    <p>
      Cloudflare Germany GmbH, Rosental 7, c/o Mindspace, 80331 München, Germany
      (Cloudflare)
    </p>
    <p>
      I use the Content Delivery Network (CDN) provided by Cloudflare to
      enhance the security and delivery speed of this website. This aligns with
      my legitimate interest (Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR). A CDN is a network
      of globally distributed servers capable of delivering optimized content to
      website users. For this purpose, personal data may be processed in
      Cloudflare's server log files. Please refer to the "Hosting" section for
      more details.
      <br />
      Cloudflare acts as a recipient of your personal data and serves as a
      processor on my behalf. This is also in line with my legitimate interest
      under Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR, as it allows me to not operate a CDN
      myself.
      <br />
      You have the right to object to the processing. Whether the objection is successful
      will be determined through a balance of interests assessment.
      <br />
      The processing of data specified in this section is neither legally nor contractually
      required. However, the functionality of the website cannot be guaranteed without
      this processing.
      <br />
      Your personal data will be stored by Cloudflare for as long as necessary
      for the stated purposes.
      <br />
      For more information on objection and deletion options against Cloudflare, please
      refer to:
      <Link href="https://www.cloudflare.com/de-de/cloudflare-customer-dpa/">
        Cloudflare DPA
      </Link>
      <br />
      Cloudflare has implemented compliance measures for international data transfers.
      These apply to all global activities where Cloudflare processes personal data
      of individuals in the EU. These measures are based on the EU Standard Contractual
      Clauses (SCCs). For more information, please visit:
      <Link
        href="https://www.cloudflare.com/cloudflare_customer_SCCs-German.pdf"
      >
        www.cloudflare.com/cloudflare_customer_SCCs-German.pdf
      </Link>
      .
    </p>

    <h2>External Links</h2>
    <p>
      This website links to external websites such as GitHub, LinkedIn, Cal.com,
      and project pages. If you follow those links, the respective third-party
      providers are responsible for their own data processing.
    </p>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  section.privacy {
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;

    h1 {
      font-size: 3em;
      margin-top: 4rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 2em;
      margin-top: 3rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    h3 {
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    a {
      display: inline-block;
    }

    p {
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      max-width: 60rem;
      color: #ececec;
    }
  }
</style>
